            <thetext>The config key &#39;themes&#39; has a misleading name. It is just a map to take macro definitions that will be used when processing #asset hints in JS source files. There is nothing particluar about themes in it (although it can be used to work with icon themes). But there is too much confusion with e.g. the qx.theme setting. So the key should be more aptly named, e.g. like &#39;asset-macros&#39;.</thetext>
